commits.message:
Improve active profiles API (#92)

Adds an ActiveProfilesBuilder with a fluent API to create a list of
active profiles following the conventions laid out by Annotated
Container. It allows for conditionally adding profiles in addition to
the 'default' profile. The expected use case for this construct is when
you're programatically creating your list of active profiles.

Also adds an ActiveProfilesParser and implementation that parses a CSV
list of active profiles. For example, the string 'default,dev,local'
would result in an array of ['default', 'dev', 'local']. The intended
use case for this construct is when you have the profiles set as a
string in an environment variable or some other hard-coded
configuration.

issue.title: Create better API for assigning active profiles when creating a Container

milestone.title: v0.5 Release
milestone.description: This release will be focused on improving the test suites and testing utilities.

issue.body:
## Problem

While active profiles are simple an array of strings, and that shouldn't be changed, there is a critical assumption about the contents of this array that's very important. Namely, that active profiles include the `default` profile. This is the profile that is implicitly assigned to all services that don't explicitly set a profile. Without the `default` profile being active it is highly likely that your Container will simply not function the way you expect it to in the vast majority of use cases.

While we could throw exceptions or implicitly add the `default` profile to the list of active profiles we take the stance that AnnotatedContainer should not be manipulating what profiles are active or not. While _most_ cases without a `default` profile is probably an error there might be a valid reason for not including it. This implementation should improve how active profiles are determined, but not change the way profiles are currently handled within the parsing module, definition conversion module, nor container factory modules.

## Solution

Resolving the issues around specifying active profiles will take multiple approaches. The first will be the creation of an interface `ActiveProfilesParser` that will provide a method to parse a string into an array of profiles. A concrete implementation `CsvActiveProfilesParser` will parse a comma-separated value into an array. The second will be the creation of a class `ActiveProfilesBuilder` that will provide a fluent API for generating an array of profiles.

issue.title: Add more thorough testing when Services are given arbitrary names

milestone.title: v0.5 Release
milestone.description: This release will be focused on improving the test suites and testing utilities.

issue.body:
The current testing around using arbitrary names to identify a service is missing several key components. Additions should be made to the existing fixtures and test suite to include testing the following scenarios.

- [x] Confirm that calling `ContainerInterface::get` with the FCQN and the arbitrary name results in the same shared object.
- [ ] Confirm that able to use `#[Inject]` on a type-hint representing a service with an arbitrary name and the correct implementation is injected.
